Answers to questions:
In the trees package I created 4 classes: Flora, Fruit, Leaf, Stem.
Flora class is in charge of planting trees in the game's world. It creates instances(composition) of
stems, leaves and fruits of all trees and randomly chooses where to plant every tree.
Fruit class represents a fruit game object that is part of a tree. It adds energy to the avatar when they
collide, and disappears for a full day cycle, and then returns to the game. It also updates it's color when
the avatar jumps.
Leaf class represents a leaf game object that is part of a tree. It rotates it's angle in 90 degrees whenever
the avatar jumps.
Stem class represents a stem game object that is part of a tree. Once the avatar jumps, it updates it's color
to a random different brown shade.
I did not use any design pattern for this part.

